Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.54,0:02:30.58,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,{\an8}Wh-What?! {Line 19-21 copied from episode 17 -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.58,0:02:36.80,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,{\an8}The hand I severed became \Na living creature and invaded your body!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.84,0:02:41.18,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,As you can see, it became a piranha!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:54.19,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It has a large hole in its torso \Ngoing up to its neck...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.19,0:02:55.78,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...yet it can still move?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:02:59.90,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,Wh-What's wrong, Babyface?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.90,0:03:01.32,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,Answer me! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.32,0:03:06.29,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,This is actual shit left behind by the tortoise!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.29,0:03:09.75,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,Why am I the one \Nwho has to deal with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.75,0:03:11.67,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.67,0:03:14.00,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,This pain in my heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.50,0:03:16.88,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,You'll pay for this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.51,0:03:21.09,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,...by dying in disgrace!\N I'll make sure of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.51,0:03:27.06,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,If Buccellati and Trish won't\N return to normal unless I defeat you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.56,0:03:28.93,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...then that's what I'll do!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.39,0:03:30.60,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You can't escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.60,0:03:32.65,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'm going for your head this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.65,0:03:34.56,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,Just try me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.15,0:03:36.86,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,...you son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.78,0:03:41.03,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,This is bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.03,0:03:45.58,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,The downside to its automatic tracking \Nis that it doesn't always listen to me. {check this one Toni, it changes the meaning quite a bit}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.45,0:03:48.79,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,Asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.79,0:03:52.33,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You've already gouged out \Nthree pieces of my body...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.33,0:03:54.21,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I know the range of your attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.13,0:04:04.05,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Did its range...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.05,0:04:05.72,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...just extend itself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.14,0:04:12.81,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,He grew taller?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.81,0:04:15.44,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,His anger must have caused him to grow!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.44,0:04:16.90,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,Di molto!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.90,0:04:19.69,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,I knew that woman was\N the right person to be his mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.82,0:04:24.61,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,Simple is best.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.61,0:04:28.83,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,I'm gonna kill this asshole {\i1}my{\i0} way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.37,0:04:31.12,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Bring it back, Gold Experience!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.54,0:04:33.16,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.25,0:04:37.09,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Muda!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.34,0:04:40.42,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,A direct hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.93,0:04:45.59,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,Take a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.59,0:04:47.97,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,You didn't hit my head!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.43,0:04:51.14,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,I win! It's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.02,0:04:54.14,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I told you, it's pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.52,0:05:00.53,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,Wh-What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.53,0:05:02.03,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Look again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.03,0:05:06.36,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The object that returned to\N Gold Experience wasn't its own hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.74,0:05:09.41,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It was the motorcycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.41,0:05:12.62,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I imbued the motorcycle with life \Nand had it return as a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.00,0:05:20.13,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You just assimilated the \Nmotorcycle into your body...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.71,0:05:21.92,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...as a part of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:24.09,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,This is nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.09,0:05:27.18,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,I'll just split apart and get away aga{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.18,0:05:28.47,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Think about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.47,0:05:30.47,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Motorcycles contain gasoline.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.26,0:05:36.64,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'm fairly certain I can create a large enough explosion\N to prevent you from escaping by splitting yourself apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.31,0:05:39.31,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.07,0:05:51.78,Main,Babyface,0,0,0,,Sizzling... Burning...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.33,0:05:57.50,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It seems as though doing things \Nyour way was pointless... in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.75,0:06:02.63,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,I-It disappeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.63,0:06:04.17,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,My contact with it disappeared?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.17,0:06:06.26,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,Damn! This is absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.26,0:06:07.76,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,That new guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.51,0:06:14.52,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,He did it...{It really speaks to how accustomed these guys are to dealing with crazy shit that THIS is his entire reaction... -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.49,0:06:28.32,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,It should be somewhere around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.95,0:06:32.95,Main,Guy,0,0,0,,My car's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.74,0:06:32.95,Secondary,Lady,0,0,0,,Where's my car? Who stole it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.95,0:06:35.91,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,That's Melone's motorcycle...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.91,0:06:42.38,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,I was told to ask around, \Ndig up whatever dirt will help me find them...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.38,0:06:44.75,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,The digging part I get.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:46.84,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,It makes perfect sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.84,0:06:50.09,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,It's like digging for stuff hidden in the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.80,0:06:54.51,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,But why the flying fuck \Nwould you dig up dirt?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.51,0:06:56.02,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Dirt is fucking everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.02,0:06:57.48,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Jesus fuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.48,0:06:58.77,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,What fucking bullshit is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.77,0:07:01.23,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Who the fuck digs up dirt looking for dirt?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.23,0:07:03.65,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Do I look fucking retarded?!\N Goddammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.40,0:07:09.36,Narrator,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Hey, Melone! \NI can't find shit on Buccellati and his crew!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.82,0:07:13.24,Narrator,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,You getting this? Hello?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.24,0:07:14.95,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,I can hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.95,0:07:17.54,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,But I'm not giving up just yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.04,0:07:20.50,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,I still have Buccellati's blood!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.50,0:07:22.88,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,I can produce as many Juniors as we need!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.71,0:07:25.84,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,I'll send one in pursuit right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.13,0:07:29.30,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,You'd better, Melone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:31.80,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,We need to take the new guy more seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:33.76,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,He should be the first one we eliminate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.60,0:07:38.22,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,I'll find an even better mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.10,0:07:42.69,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,...and create a powered-up, completely invincible...{I really don't like this split but given the long pause he takes and how "Junior" is the first word he says after said pause... it's kinda inevitable I guess -.- -Starfish}{I completely agree. I hate this split. I tried to combine it but that pause is just a bit too long D: -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.23,0:07:47.15,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,...Junior who will track them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.69,0:07:51.61,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.36,0:07:53.82,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,It looked like a snake...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.12,0:07:55.91,Narrator,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,What? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.91,0:07:58.29,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,What is a snake doing at a station in Rome?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.21,0:08:04.67,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,I-It's burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.08,0:08:08.21,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,This is... the new guy's ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.21,0:08:10.88,Main,Melone,0,0,0,,He must have used the Junior's corpse to{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.60,0:08:19.22,Narrator,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.22,0:08:22.31,Narrator,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Hey, Melone!\N What the fuck?! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:29.94,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The venomous snake I sent to Roma Termini Station \Njust turned back into part of the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:33.20,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,The user is eliminated. \NThat makes five.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.20,0:08:37.78,Main,Fugo,0,0,0,,If our intel is correct, \Nonly two members of the Hitman Team remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.78,0:08:39.99,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We still gotta be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.37,0:08:42.46,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Now let's get to Venice already!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.46,0:08:46.67,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Now Melone, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.84,0:08:50.17,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Fuck! Fuck! Fuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.17,0:08:51.80,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Motherfucker!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.59,0:08:55.22,Narrator,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Hello?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.22,0:08:58.30,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,It's me.\N I managed to finish the analysis.
Comment: 0,0:08:58.30,0:08:58.97,Narrator,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.47,0:09:01.43,Main,Risotto,0,0,0,,I'm sending you the data as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.36,0:09:12.40,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,We just received a new order from the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.36,0:09:16.78,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Abbacchio, could you come over here next to the chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.78,0:09:17.49,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Me? {No, the other Abbacchio}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.45,0:09:20.95,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Here's the order.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.95,0:09:27.04,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,"Have Abbacchio use his Moody Blues \Nnear the dining chair and rewind to just over 14 hours ago."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.04,0:09:31.55,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Someone else was inside the tortoise before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.55,0:09:32.84,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I believe that's what he's getting at.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.17,0:09:34.59,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.59,0:09:37.09,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I'll start looking from about fifteen hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.14,0:09:45.35,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,It transformed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.10,0:09:49.61,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Hey, that old dude looks familiar!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.61,0:09:51.36,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,That's the capo, Mr. Pericolo!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.36,0:09:56.15,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,So he was the one who placed the tortoise near the water fountain at Naples Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.15,0:10:00.07,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,And approximately fourteen hours ago,\N he entered this tortoise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.83,0:10:02.04,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,I'm continuing the replay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.41,0:10:08.50,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Buccellati and team, \NI will now give you your final order.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.21,0:10:10.25,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Final order?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.71,0:10:16.01,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,I'm using this method to give you the message\N in order to prevent it from falling into the wrong hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.01,0:10:19.93,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,What I'm about to tell you is of utmost importance and must remain between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.93,0:10:23.47,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,I'm going to tell you how to \Nhand Trish off to the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.10,0:10:25.18,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,How we're going...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.18,0:10:26.56,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,...to hand her over? {Lol this is such a One Piece moment. I can totally imagine one of the straw hats starting the sentence and the other finishing it thanks to their psychic connection. Now all we need is a large mob of random people yelling very long lines of dialogue in perfect timing -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.19,0:10:28.98,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Listen closely, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.98,0:10:31.19,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Once you've safely arrived in Venice...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.19,0:10:36.86,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,...go to this sculpture and retrieve \Nthe OA-DISC that's inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.86,0:10:41.03,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,It contains data that will instruct you on how to hand her over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.16,0:10:43.83,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,Hey! He burned it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.83,0:10:45.50,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Abbacchio, pause it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.50,0:10:46.41,Main,Abbacchio,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.41,0:10:51.17,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure this is \Nthe entrance to Venice...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.50,0:10:53.25,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Right in front of Santa Lucia Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.63,0:10:55.13,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,The lion statue is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.34,0:10:57.72,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.72,0:11:00.55,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Obtain the OA-DISC at all costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.55,0:11:03.18,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,My identity has been compromised.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.18,0:11:09.94,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Nothing is more important right now \Nthan bringing Trish to her father, the boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.94,0:11:12.31,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,No evidence can be left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:20.53,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,Thanks to the boss, I've been able to live a wealthy, blessed, and fulfilling life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:23.03,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,My mission is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.12,0:11:28.50,Main,Pericolo,0,0,0,,From the bottom of my heart, \NI pray for your success.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.17,0:11:36.25,Main,Narancia,0,0,0,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.10,0:11:45.43,Main,Bruno,0,0,0,,Mr. Pericolo...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.02,0:11:58.28,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,They should have received the order by now. {IT MAKES ME SO HAPPY TO SEE DIAVOLO AS THE LISTED ACTOR AAAAAAAAAAH -Gyro}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.28,0:12:07.74,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Obtaining the disc, let alone reaching me, \Nwill prove difficult for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.75,0:12:11.25,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,The most important thing is \Nwhat awaits at the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.96,0:12:15.29,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,Bring my daughter Trish here...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.63,0:12:19.51,Main,Diavolo,0,0,0,,...to Venice.
Comment: 0,0:12:23.13,0:12:23.18,Main,,0,0,0,,C
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.97,0:12:32.27,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,The fortress city of the sea, \Nfloating amidst the morning haze: Venice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.27,0:12:36.81,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,There is only one way to get there \Nby car from the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.81,0:12:41.65,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,It is a bridge which stretches for 3.5 kilometers \Nover the sea known as the Ponte della Libertà. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ponte_della_Libert%C3%A0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.07,0:12:44.53,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,The station lies just beyond it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:48.99,Narrator,Narrator,0,0,0,,The lion statue where the target disc is hidden \Ncan be found in a square there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.58,0:12:57.04,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Giorno, so far I haven't seen anyone tailing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:12:59.71,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yes. No one in front of us, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.71,0:13:01.59,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The city is still asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.59,0:13:03.72,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,We're the only car on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.22,0:13:06.80,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Why do the windows keep fogging up so quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.89,0:13:13.27,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.27,0:13:14.56,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,My apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.56,0:13:16.60,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The tires just slipped a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.60,0:13:18.82,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,On a straight bridge like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.82,0:13:21.73,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Try to be more careful! \NDo you even have a license?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.73,0:13:23.74,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,No. I'm only fifteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.45,0:13:31.12,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What's that thing stuck on the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.12,0:13:33.16,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.16,0:13:36.67,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I didn't notice it when \NI was looking outside earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.67,0:13:38.46,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,No, wait a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.79,0:13:40.84,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,That shape...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.84,0:13:42.17,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's... a finger!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.59,0:13:49.51,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Let's open the windows a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.51,0:13:52.81,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The windows are fogging up from the \Ntemperature difference inside and out of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.73,0:13:56.35,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Wh-What?! \NWhat's with this wind pressure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.94,0:14:01.65,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,At first, we were frozen with fear... But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.07,0:14:09.32,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,With the help of a computer, it wasn't too hard to recreate the ashes that were lying next to Pericolo in the photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.78,0:14:11.20,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,You guys fucking clueless!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.95,0:14:15.21,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,You'll never get away from the Hitman Team!{I'm just WAITING for him to call them "Damn nerds" and create explosions from his hands at this point. -Starfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.21,0:14:18.46,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's an enemy! \NThey got on the roof of the car without us realizing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.46,0:14:21.96,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Mista, what are you doing? \NShoot the enemy through the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.96,0:14:25.80,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,The car is being chilled crazy fast right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.80,0:14:33.18,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,It's so fast that my finger froze to the window and snapped off before I even felt the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.10,0:14:38.06,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,If I don't peel my face off the window, \Nmy brain will freeze up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.06,0:14:40.90,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Not sure I'm ready to sacrifice my face, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.52,0:14:43.90,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Where's the tortoise?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.90,0:14:46.49,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,I don't see the tortoise in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.74,0:14:50.37,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,You two aren't with Trish and Buccellati?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.37,0:14:53.62,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,If you went through the trouble of splitting up...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.62,0:14:55.08,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.08,0:14:59.08,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,You must be on a mission\N to get something {\i1}really{\i0} important!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.08,0:15:00.75,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,The location in the picture...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.75,0:15:02.88,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,It has to be at the station in Venice!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.25,0:15:06.67,Thoughts,Mista,0,0,0,,Blood finally spurted from my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.63,0:15:11.09,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Yeehaw!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.18,0:15:16.18,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,I-Ice!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.60,0:15:19.85,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,He covered himself in ice and \Nfroze himself to the roof of the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.85,0:15:23.02,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,The bullets can't get through to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.69,0:15:24.61,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,What the...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.61,0:15:27.82,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,N-No! \NWe're starting to freeze, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.90,0:15:30.53,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.53,0:15:32.03,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Number Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.03,0:15:32.87,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.33,0:15:37.04,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Number Two! \NNumber Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.91,0:15:39.87,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.83,0:15:46.55,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,A-All I did was blink, \Nand now my eyelashes are stuck together!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.09,0:15:50.63,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,He must have positioned himself \Non the roof on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.97,0:15:54.72,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The car is currently going \Neighty kilometers per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.72,0:15:56.10,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.10,0:15:59.31,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,It's similar to being stuck in \Ntwenty meter per second wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.73,0:16:04.23,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The effective temperature drops by 1° Celsius \Nfor every meter of wind velocity...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.48,0:16:08.15,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...so the air around us has chilled to -20° Celsius!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.15,0:16:09.57,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Then stop the damn car!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.57,0:16:12.36,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Why the hell are you still flooring it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.61,0:16:14.91,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm trying to...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.91,0:16:18.66,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,But the brake pedal is frozen and won't go down!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.66,0:16:20.16,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I'm losing the steering wheel, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.16,0:16:23.08,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The engine is still running and seemingly won't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.59,0:16:30.63,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The surface of the car has to have \Nreached -100° Celsius by now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.92,0:16:34.64,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,And at incredible speed! \NSo this is... the enemy's ability!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.60,0:16:41.27,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Th-The blood that was spurting out of my hand froze...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.48,0:16:46.31,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,And the moisture from my breathing\N caused my nostrils to freeze together...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.77,0:16:49.40,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,And now my lips...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.40,0:16:50.99,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Shit! I can't breathe!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.44,0:16:53.03,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,S-Stop the car, Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.03,0:16:55.37,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Can't you can turn the car \Ninto a frog or something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.37,0:16:57.49,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Use your ability somehow!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.49,0:16:59.99,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I've already tried that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.99,0:17:04.29,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,But there are no organisms \Nthat can be born at -100° Celsius!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.34,0:17:10.38,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,You know about Paris, France?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.38,0:17:12.92,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,In English, they pronounce it "Paris"...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.92,0:17:16.47,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,But everyone else pronounces it \Nwithout the "s" sound, like the French do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.47,0:17:20.52,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,But with Venezia, everyone pronounces \Nit the English way, "Venice".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.89,0:17:24.69,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,As in, {\i1}The Merchant of Venice{\i0} \Nand {\i1}Death in Venice{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.27,0:17:30.23,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Why isn't the title {\i1}Death in Venezia?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.23,0:17:31.82,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Are they fucking mocking me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.82,0:17:34.70,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Use the Italian word \Nsince it takes place here, fuckheads!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.70,0:17:37.37,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,This shit pisses me off!\N Are they seriously fucking mocking me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.37,0:17:38.95,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Fucking morons!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.91,0:17:46.83,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Looks like they're starting \Nto have trouble driving...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.83,0:17:48.42,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Mista...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:52.21,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,My Gold Experience needs heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.21,0:17:56.05,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,So unfortunately, the most I can do for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.34,0:17:59.01,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,...is pick up these bullets...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.64,0:18:03.43,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,You won't be able to fill the car\N with any more holes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.43,0:18:06.06,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,I'll just freeze you to an even lower temp{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.90,0:18:16.24,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Bullets create heat from being fired, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.24,0:18:19.74,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,So by firing the bullets Giorno picked up for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.74,0:18:21.03,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...I'm making heat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.03,0:18:25.79,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,I guess I'll go ahead and \Ndo the honors for Giorno while I'm at it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.37,0:18:28.63,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Gold Experience!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.97,0:18:37.26,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.26,0:18:44.31,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Plant roots have the energy to prop up \Nasphalt in roads and even shatter rocks!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.31,0:18:47.52,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Keep hold of the steering wheel, Giorno! \NWe're gonna make a break for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.57,0:19:01.07,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,So that must be the new guy's ability Melone mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.07,0:19:03.41,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,But you're not getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.33,0:19:08.87,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Seriously? What an asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.87,0:19:10.83,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He's still coming after us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.83,0:19:15.34,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,I, Ghiaccio,{He's Dio now. Deal with it. (Well actually I just wanted to keep this in to make it so his name isn't said only ONCE, before we even see him.) -Starfish} will be taking \Nwhatever's at the station, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.84,0:19:19.72,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,You're wasting your bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.72,0:19:27.31,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,My ability, White Album, freezes the moisture in the air\N to an extremely low temperature, letting me wear it like armor!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.52,0:19:35.61,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,Not only does it allow me to skate, \Nit also gives me enough power to shrug off your pathetic bullets!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.23,0:19:37.69,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Step on it, Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.69,0:19:39.28,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I can't go any faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.28,0:19:41.07,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,The tires are still slipping!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.07,0:19:44.12,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,But worst of all, they know our plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.12,0:19:47.54,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,They don't know where the tortoise and Trish are...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.54,0:19:51.04,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...so if you look on the bright side, \Nwe're not totally fucked.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.04,0:19:54.09,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,Optimistic as usual, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.09,0:19:55.30,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,You're a strange man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.59,0:19:57.55,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He's coming! \NFloor it! Faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.55,0:19:58.84,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,I told you, I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.84,0:20:01.38,Main,Giorno,0,0,0,,If we slip, we'll lose even more sp{\fscx300}-{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.38,0:20:03.97,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Just do it, dammit! \NFloor it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.97,0:20:06.35,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,I told you, you're wasting your time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.35,0:20:08.89,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Number Three and Number Two \Nup on the roof, come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.40,0:20:17.69,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Here's hoping you share a long kiss...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.69,0:20:22.45,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,...with Madame Concrete. \NAll the speed you've built up should make it extra passionate!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.83,0:20:28.16,Main,Sex Pistols,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.54,0:20:30.25,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Good. We lost him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.25,0:20:33.17,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Now get us into the city \Nand head straight for the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.04,0:20:40.63,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Before he can catch up to us, \Nwe'll get our hands on the disc and hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.17,0:20:41.88,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,Giorno!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.89,0:20:45.72,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,You're not getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.72,0:20:50.02,Main,Ghiaccio,0,0,0,,There's no way you fucks are\N making it to the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.02,0:20:52.77,Main,Mista,0,0,0,,He's freezing the moisture from the car's exhaust!
